    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/retail-management/RMG/902.html" title="RMG 902 - Franchising" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">RMG 902</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Franchising</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">The focus of this course is on business format franchising - the transfer of a particular business format or way of conducting business. The costs and benefits of franchising from both the franchisee's and franchiser's point of view will be explored.  Franchiser/franchisee communication and relationship will be discussed.  Students will examine how to determine the feasibility of a franchise opportunity, the legal dimensions of franchising, characteristics of the typical franchisee, and international franchising as a means of expansion.</div>
	
	
