    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/retail-management/RMG/916.html" title="RMG 916 - Managing B2B Channels" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">RMG 916</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Managing B2B Channels</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This course will explore how organizations leverage channels of distribution for value creation and competitive advantage.  It delves into strategies that companies use to bring products and services from their point of origin to their point of consumption.  Product proliferation, media fragmentation, retailer power and the internet have required excellence in channel design and management.  The course will cover key concepts and strategies related to channel management, in light of traditional and new channels of distribution.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListWeight"><span class="courseInfoLabels">GPA weight: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">1.00</span></div>
	
	
